  {
    "ts": "2026-04-09T16:44:00+00:00",
    "headline": "Brown-Forman Stock Soars. Jack Daniel’s Maker Has Another Potential Bidder, Says Report.",
    "summary": "Fellow Louisville liquor company Sazerac recently approached Brown-Forman about a potential deal, The Wall Street Journal reported Thursday, citing people familiar with the matter.  Brown-Forman’s  class B stock jumped 12% to $30.01 shortly after the report broke.  Sazerac’s interest comes after Brown-Forman and French spirits company  Pernod Ricard  confirmed last month that they were engaged in discussions about a potential “merger of equals.” Brown-Forman stock, which has been in free fall since late 2020, jumped after that news and has held steady in the weeks since.",
    "url": "https://www.barrons.com/articles/brown-forman-stock-jack-daniels-sazerac-5158ddad?siteid=yhoof2&yptr=yahoo",
